pageContext.claim: “Thousands of uncounted ballots were discovered in Floyd, Fayette, and Walton counties weeks after the election, and these ballots were mostly from Trump voters. They weren't counted. They were from Trump voters,”
pageContext.analysis: Some 6,000 votes that had not be counted in Georgia were discovered as part of a hand recount. But these were votes for both Trump and Biden. The addition of these votes did not change the outcome but Biden’s lead over Trump narrowed from 14,156 votes to 12,781 votes.
